/-!
# Phase B-خ± (paper-faithful) strong existential matching

This module is **Phase B-خ±** of the CPSV16/CPSV21 fundamental-theorem
clean-slate plan (issue #1725) â€” the paper-faithful strong existential
matching theorem.  It states the CPSV16 آ§II.C lines 1182â€“1186 *Step 1*
conclusion directly on the original (un-dropped) pair `(P, Q)` of
BNT canonical forms, iterated over each sector `k` of `Q` that carries
a unit-modulus copy.

## Paper anchor

CPSV16 (arXiv:1606.00608) آ§II.C lines 1182â€“1186, the *entire* "Step 1"
of the proof of Theorem `II_cor2` (verbatim):

> "Let us first consider $B_k$ for some given $k$.  It is not possible
> that $\langle V^{(N)}(B_k)|V^{(N)}(A_j)\rangle \to 0$ as $N\to\infty$
> for all $j$, since otherwise the MPV generated by $A$ and $B$ could
> not be proportional for all $N$ (Lemma `Lem1`).  Thus, according to
> Corollary `eqV`, there must exist one $j_k$ such that
> $|V^{(N)}(B_k)\rangle = e^{i\phi_k N} |V^{(N)}(A_{j_k})\rangle$.
> According to Lemma `equalMPS` we have $B_k = e^{i\phi_k} X_k A_{j_k} X_k^{-1}$."

The paper's "given $k$" is *iterated externally* over each unit-block
sector of `Q` (those with at least one unit-modulus weight, per the
CPSV16 آ§II.A line-246 normalization which is recorded **globally** â€”
not per-block â€” in `IsBNTCanonicalForm.weight_unit_exists`).  Non-unit
blocks contribute coefficients that decay exponentially and so do not
constrain the matching; the paper restricts attention to the
"physical" (unit-modulus carrying) blocks.

## Scope (Phase B-خ±)

The result is a **single `âˆ€ k, âˆƒ j` existential statement** on the
original pair, with the paper's "given $k$" hypothesis explicitly
encoded as the unit-modulus existential.  There is **no recursion**,
no `dropSector` usage, and no combined-LI obligation on a partial
union: the entire proof routes through the existing
`exists_unit_block_match_of_sameMPV` lemma (which itself routes
through the full-family combined LI `combined_family_eventually_li`,
`PaperBNT/Api.lean`).

The downstream Phase B-خ² (bijective matching) will apply this theorem
twice â€” once with `(P, Q)` and once with `(Q, P)` â€” to derive
`P.basisCount = Q.basisCount` on the unit-block subset and the per-pair
bijection / gauge data.

## Proof strategy (route B of the audit memo)

Given a sector `k` of `Q` with a unit-modulus weight, apply the
existing `exists_unit_block_match_of_sameMPV` (`PaperBNT/DominantMatch`,
post-Phase-A rename in PR #1726) **with `P` and `Q` swapped**:

* feed `hQ`, `hP` (in that order);
* supply `hP_pos : 0 < P.basisCount` from `hP.weight_unit_exists`
  (which exists globally on `P`);
* supply the unit-modulus witness on `Q`'s `k` (the hypothesis of this
  theorem); and
* supply `SameMPVâ‚‚ Q.toTensor P.toTensor` via the trivial symmetric
  flip of `hEqual` (pointwise `.symm`).

The result is a `jâ‚€ : Fin P.basisCount` with `Q.basisDim k = P.basisDim jâ‚€`,
a gauge-phase equivalence in the `Q â†’ P` cast direction, and a
non-decaying overlap in the `(Q.basis k, P.basis jâ‚€)` order.  Two
local helpers (`gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast` and
`tendsto_mpvOverlap_zero_swap`) flip those into the paper-stated
`(P, Q)`-ordered conclusion.

No `sorry`, no `axiom`, no `unsafe`.
-/

