/-! ### Local helpers: symmetry of `GaugePhaseEquiv` across a bond-dim cast -/

/-- Symmetry of `GaugePhaseEquiv` at a fixed bond dimension.

`GaugePhaseEquiv A B` says there exist a gauge `X âˆˆ GL` and a nonzero
scalar `خ¶` such that `B i = خ¶ â€¢ (X * A i * Xâپ»آ¹)` for every physical
index `i`.  Conjugating by `Xâپ»آ¹` and scaling by `خ¶âپ»آ¹` gives the
reversed identity `A i = خ¶âپ»آ¹ â€¢ (Xâپ»آ¹ * B i * X)`, i.e.
`GaugePhaseEquiv B A`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_symm_same_dim {d D : â„•} {A B : MPSTensor d D}
    (h : GaugePhaseEquiv A B) : GaugePhaseEquiv B A := by
  classical
  obtain âں¨X, خ¶, hخ¶, hrelâں© := h
  refine âں¨Xâپ»آ¹, خ¶âپ»آ¹, inv_ne_zero hخ¶, ?_âں©
  intro i
  -- From `B i = خ¶ â€¢ (X * A i * Xâپ»آ¹)` derive `A i = خ¶âپ»آ¹ â€¢ (Xâپ»آ¹ * B i * X)`.
  have hBi := hrel i
  -- Abbreviations for the matrix coercions.
  set XM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚ := (X : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
  set XinvM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚ :=
    ((Xâپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
  have hXX : XinvM * XM = (1 : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚) := by
    have hU : (Xâپ»آ¹ * X : GL (Fin D) â„‚) = 1 := by simp
    have hUval :
        ((Xâپ»آ¹ * X : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
          = ((1 : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚) :=
      congrArg Units.val hU
    simp only [Units.val_mul, Units.val_one] at hUval
    exact hUval
  have hXX' : XM * XinvM = (1 : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚) := by
    have hU : (X * Xâپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) = 1 := by simp
    have hUval :
        ((X * Xâپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
          = ((1 : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚) :=
      congrArg Units.val hU
    simp only [Units.val_mul, Units.val_one] at hUval
    exact hUval
  -- Inverse-of-inverse: `(Xâپ»آ¹)âپ»آ¹ = X` for units.
  have hInvInv : ((Xâپ»آ¹)âپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) = X := inv_inv X
  -- The desired identity: `A i = خ¶âپ»آ¹ â€¢ (Xâپ»آ¹ * B i * X)`.
  -- Multiply `hBi : B i = خ¶ â€¢ (X * A i * Xâپ»آ¹)` on the left by `Xâپ»آ¹` and on
  -- the right by `X`:
  --   Xâپ»آ¹ * B i * X = خ¶ â€¢ (Xâپ»آ¹ * X * A i * Xâپ»آ¹ * X) = خ¶ â€¢ (1 * A i * 1) = خ¶ â€¢ A i.
  have hSandwich :
      XinvM * B i * XM = خ¶ â€¢ A i := by
    calc
      XinvM * B i * XM
          = XinvM * (خ¶ â€¢ (XM * A i * XinvM)) * XM := by rw [hBi]
      _ = خ¶ â€¢ (XinvM * (XM * A i * XinvM) * XM) := by
            simp
      _ = خ¶ â€¢ ((XinvM * XM) * A i * (XinvM * XM)) := by
            simp [Matrix.mul_assoc]
      _ = خ¶ â€¢ A i := by rw [hXX]; simp
  -- Now divide by `خ¶`.
  have hAi : A i = خ¶âپ»آ¹ â€¢ (XinvM * B i * XM) := by
    have := congrArg (fun M => (خ¶âپ»آ¹ : â„‚) â€¢ M) hSandwich
    simp only [smul_smul, inv_mul_cancelâ‚€ hخ¶, one_smul] at this
    exact this.symm
  -- Repackage with the inverse of `Xâپ»آ¹` being `X`.
  -- The goal expects `((Xâپ»آ¹)âپ»آ¹ : GL).val = X.val`.
  change A i = خ¶âپ»آ¹ â€¢ (XinvM * B i *
    (((Xâپ»آ¹)âپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚))
  simpa [hInvInv, XM, XinvM] using hAi

/-- Symmetry of `GaugePhaseEquiv` across a bond-dim cast: if the cast
maps the *right-hand* tensor into the *left-hand* space, then we may
flip both the cast direction and the equivalence direction.

The two forms are mathematically the same statement (after eliminating
the cast by `subst`), but the cast routing differs at the term level,
so we record this as an explicit helper used inside
`forall_unit_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast {d Dâ‚پ Dâ‚‚ : â„•}
    (h : Dâ‚پ = Dâ‚‚) {A : MPSTensor d Dâ‚پ} {B : MPSTensor d Dâ‚‚}
    (hGP : GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h.symm) B) A) :
    GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h) A) B := by
  subst h
  -- After `subst`, both casts reduce to identity.
  simpa using gaugePhaseEquiv_symm_same_dim (by simpa using hGP)

/-! ### Phase B-خ± main theorem: paper-faithful strong existential matching -/

/-- **CPSV16 آ§II.C lines 1182â€“1186 Step 1 (paper-faithful Phase B-خ±).**

For every sector `k` of `Q` that carries at least one unit-modulus
weight (the CPSV16 آ§II.A line-246 hypothesis, applied at `k`), there
exists a sector `j` of `P` of equal bond dimension, gauge-phase
equivalent to `Q.basis k` after the dimension cast, and with
non-decaying cross-overlap.

This is the paper's Step 1 contrapositive of `Lem1` (CPSV16 lines
1131â€“1133, combined LI on the **FULL** `{A^{[j]}} âˆھ {B^{[k]}}` family),
**iterated externally** over each unit-block sector `k` of `Q`.  No
recursion on a smaller `SectorDecomposition`, no `dropSector` usage,
no combined LI on a partial union â€” only the weak existential
(packaged as `exists_unit_block_match_of_sameMPV` in
`PaperBNT/DominantMatch.lean`) applied at each sector.

The unit-block restriction on `k` is paper-faithful: the CPSV16 آ§II.A
line-246 normalization is recorded globally on the two-layer `(j, q)`
indexing of the BNT display (not per-block), so non-unit-block sectors
may exist in principle.  Such "ghost" blocks have coefficients
`Q.coeff N k = âˆ‘_q (Q.weight k q)^N` that decay exponentially to zero,
contribute nothing to the thermodynamic state, and are not constrained
by the matching (the FT cannot reconstruct them from `P` alone).  The
downstream Phase B-خ² bijective-matching layer applies this theorem
twice (with `P, Q` swapped) to derive `g_a = g_b` on the unit-block
subset and the per-pair gauge data.

Proof strategy (route B of `/tmp/phase_4c_drift_audit_2026-05-14.md`):
apply `exists_unit_block_match_of_sameMPV` with the swap
`(P := Q, Q := P)`, feed `hQ`, `hP`, `hP_pos`, the unit-modulus
witness on `Q`, and the pointwise-symmetric `SameMPVâ‚‚` flip
`fun N دƒ => (hEqual N دƒ).symm`.  Re-orient the resulting conclusion
via `gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast` and `tendsto_mpvOverlap_zero_swap`.

Paper anchor: CPSV16 آ§II.C lines 1182â€“1186 (arXiv:1606.00608);
`Lem1` at CPSV16 lines 1131â€“1133.  Iteration of the paper's
"given $k$" is encoded as the outer `âˆ€ k`. -/
theorem forall_unit_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV
    {P Q : SectorDecomposition d}
    (hP : IsBNTCanonicalForm P) (hQ : IsBNTCanonicalForm Q)
    (hEqual : SameMPVâ‚‚ P.toTensor Q.toTensor) :
    âˆ€ k : Fin Q.basisCount, (âˆƒ q : Fin (Q.copies k), â€–Q.weight k qâ€– = 1) â†’
      âˆƒ (j : Fin P.basisCount) (h : P.basisDim j = Q.basisDim k),
        GaugePhaseEquiv
            (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h) (P.basis j))
            (Q.basis k) âˆ§
        آ¬ Tendsto (fun N : â„• =>
            mpvOverlap (d := d) (P.basis j) (Q.basis k) N)
          atTop (ً‌“‌ 0) := by
  classical
  intro k hUnitQ
  -- `P.basisCount > 0`: the global unit witness on `P` produces a
  -- sector index, which witnesses positivity of the basis count.
  have hP_pos : 0 < P.basisCount := by
    obtain âں¨jâ‚€, _, _âں© := hP.weight_unit_exists
    exact Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.zero_le _) jâ‚€.isLt
  -- Pointwise-symmetric flip of `SameMPVâ‚‚`: by `.symm` of each scalar
  -- equality.  No new content; just `Q â†” P` reordering.
  have hEqual_symm : SameMPVâ‚‚ Q.toTensor P.toTensor :=
    fun N دƒ => (hEqual N دƒ).symm
  -- Apply the existing Phase-A lemma with `P` and `Q` swapped.
  obtain âں¨j, hsymDim, hGE_swapped, hNonDecay_swappedâں© :=
    exists_unit_block_match_of_sameMPV
      (P := Q) (Q := P) hQ hP hP_pos k hUnitQ hEqual_symm
  -- `hsymDim : Q.basisDim k = P.basisDim j`; flip to the paper-stated
  -- `P.basisDim j = Q.basisDim k`.
  refine âں¨j, hsymDim.symm, ?_, ?_âں©
  آ· -- Gauge-phase equivalence: flip the cast direction and the
    -- equivalence direction simultaneously via `gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast`.
    -- `hGE_swapped : GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) hsymDim) (Q.basis k))
    --                                (P.basis j)`.
    -- We want `GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) hsymDim.symm)
    --                                  (P.basis j)) (Q.basis k)`.
    exact gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast hsymDim.symm
      (by
        -- `hsymDim.symm.symm = hsymDim` definitionally for `Eq`.
        simpa using hGE_swapped)
  آ· -- Tendsto symmetry: swap A and B in `mpvOverlap` preserves
    -- convergence to zero (`mpvOverlap A B N = star (mpvOverlap B A N)`).
    intro hTend
    apply hNonDecay_swapped
    exact tendsto_mpvOverlap_zero_swap (P.basis j) (Q.basis k) hTend

/-! ### Phase B-خ² local helpers: transitivity of `GaugePhaseEquiv` at a fixed bond dim

The Phase B-خ² bijective-matching proof composes two gauge-phase
equivalences `(P.basis j) â†” (Q.basis kâ‚پ)` and `(P.basis j) â†” (Q.basis kâ‚‚)`
through the common centre `P.basis j` to derive an equivalence
`(Q.basis kâ‚پ) â†” (Q.basis kâ‚‚)`.  The `basis_distinct` field of
`IsBNTCanonicalForm` then forces `kâ‚پ = kâ‚‚` (injectivity of the matching). -/

/-- Transitivity of `GaugePhaseEquiv` at a fixed bond dimension.

If `B i = خ¶â‚پ â€¢ (Xâ‚پ * A i * Xâ‚پâپ»آ¹)` and `C i = خ¶â‚‚ â€¢ (Xâ‚‚ * B i * Xâ‚‚âپ»آ¹)`,
then `C i = (خ¶â‚‚ خ¶â‚پ) â€¢ ((Xâ‚‚ Xâ‚پ) * A i * (Xâ‚‚ Xâ‚پ)âپ»آ¹)`, giving
`GaugePhaseEquiv A C` with gauge `Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ` and phase scalar `خ¶â‚‚ * خ¶â‚پ`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_trans_same_dim {d D : â„•} {A B C : MPSTensor d D}
    (hâ‚پ : GaugePhaseEquiv A B) (hâ‚‚ : GaugePhaseEquiv B C) : GaugePhaseEquiv A C := by
  classical
  obtain âں¨Xâ‚پ, خ¶â‚پ, hخ¶â‚پ, hrâ‚پâں© := hâ‚پ
  obtain âں¨Xâ‚‚, خ¶â‚‚, hخ¶â‚‚, hrâ‚‚âں© := hâ‚‚
  refine âں¨Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ, خ¶â‚‚ * خ¶â‚پ, mul_ne_zero hخ¶â‚‚ hخ¶â‚پ, ?_âں©
  intro i
  -- Abbreviations for the matrix coercions of the four GL units in play.
  set Xâ‚پM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚ :=
    ((Xâ‚پ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
  set Xâ‚‚M : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚ :=
    ((Xâ‚‚ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
  set Xâ‚پinvM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚ :=
    ((Xâ‚پâپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
  set Xâ‚‚invM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚ :=
    ((Xâ‚‚âپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)
  -- Coercion of the product `Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ` to a matrix is the matrix product.
  have hMul_val :
      (((Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ : GL (Fin D) â„‚)) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚) = Xâ‚‚M * Xâ‚پM := by
    simp [Xâ‚پM, Xâ‚‚M]
  -- Coercion of the inverse of the product is the reversed product of inverses.
  have hMulInv_val :
      (((Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ)âپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚) = Xâ‚پinvM * Xâ‚‚invM := by
    have hRev : ((Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ)âپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) = Xâ‚پâپ»آ¹ * Xâ‚‚âپ»آ¹ := mul_inv_rev Xâ‚‚ Xâ‚پ
    have := congrArg (fun U : GL (Fin D) â„‚ =>
        (U : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)) hRev
    simp [Xâ‚پinvM, Xâ‚‚invM]
  -- Compute `C i` by chaining the two equivalences.
  calc C i
      = خ¶â‚‚ â€¢ (Xâ‚‚M * B i * Xâ‚‚invM) := hrâ‚‚ i
    _ = خ¶â‚‚ â€¢ (Xâ‚‚M * (خ¶â‚پ â€¢ (Xâ‚پM * A i * Xâ‚پinvM)) * Xâ‚‚invM) := by rw [hrâ‚پ i]
    _ = خ¶â‚‚ â€¢ (خ¶â‚پ â€¢ (Xâ‚‚M * (Xâ‚پM * A i * Xâ‚پinvM) * Xâ‚‚invM)) := by
          simp [smul_smul]
    _ = (خ¶â‚‚ * خ¶â‚پ) â€¢ (Xâ‚‚M * Xâ‚پM * A i * Xâ‚پinvM * Xâ‚‚invM) := by
          simp [smul_smul, Matrix.mul_assoc]
    _ = (خ¶â‚‚ * خ¶â‚پ) â€¢ ((Xâ‚‚M * Xâ‚پM) * A i * (Xâ‚پinvM * Xâ‚‚invM)) := by
          simp [Matrix.mul_assoc]
    _ = (خ¶â‚‚ * خ¶â‚پ) â€¢
          ((((Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ : GL (Fin D) â„‚)) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚) * A i *
            (((Xâ‚‚ * Xâ‚پ)âپ»آ¹ : GL (Fin D) â„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) â„‚)) := by
          rw [hMul_val, hMulInv_val]

/-- Composition through a common centre `A`: if the cast `D = Dâ‚پ` carries
`A : MPSTensor d D` into a gauge-phase equivalence with `B : MPSTensor d Dâ‚پ`,
and similarly the cast `D = Dâ‚‚` carries `A` into a gauge-phase equivalence
with `C : MPSTensor d Dâ‚‚`, then `B` and `C` are gauge-phase equivalent
(after the dimension cast `Dâ‚پ = Dâ‚‚`).

This is the cast-aware transitivity used in Phase B-خ² to derive
`GaugePhaseEquiv (Q.basis kâ‚پ) (Q.basis kâ‚‚)` (up to cast) from two
matchings against the same `P.basis j`, before invoking `basis_distinct`
of `Q` to force `kâ‚پ = kâ‚‚`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_cast_compose_via_centre
    {d D Dâ‚پ Dâ‚‚ : â„•}
    (hâ‚پ : D = Dâ‚پ) (hâ‚‚ : D = Dâ‚‚)
    {A : MPSTensor d D} {B : MPSTensor d Dâ‚پ} {C : MPSTensor d Dâ‚‚}
    (GEâ‚پ : GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) hâ‚پ) A) B)
    (GEâ‚‚ : GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) hâ‚‚) A) C) :
    GaugePhaseEquiv
        (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) (hâ‚پ.symm.trans hâ‚‚)) B) C := by
  subst hâ‚پ
  -- After `subst hâ‚پ`, `Dâ‚پ` is replaced everywhere by `D`, the cast on
  -- `GEâ‚پ` reduces to identity, and `hâ‚‚.symm.trans hâ‚‚ = hâ‚‚`.
  subst hâ‚‚
  -- After `subst hâ‚‚`, all three tensors live in `MPSTensor d D`.
  simp only [cast_eq] at GEâ‚پ GEâ‚‚ âٹ¢
  exact gaugePhaseEquiv_trans_same_dim (gaugePhaseEquiv_symm_same_dim GEâ‚پ) GEâ‚‚

/-! ### Phase B-خ² main theorem: bijective matching by symmetry

CPSV16 آ§II.C lines 1184â€“1186, the **symmetry argument**
`g_a â‰¥ g_b âˆ§ g_b â‰¥ g_a â‡’ g_a = g_b`.

The paper-faithful Phase B-خ± theorem
`forall_unit_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV` gives one
direction: for every unit-modulus sector `k` of `Q` there exists a
sector `j` of `P` with matched bond dimension, gauge-phase equivalence
(after cast), and non-decaying cross-overlap.  Applying the SAME theorem
once more with `(P, Q)` swapped and `SameMPVâ‚‚` symmetrically flipped
gives the other direction: for every unit-modulus sector `j` of `P`
there exists a sector `k` of `Q` with the matching data.

The resulting two functions are **injective embeddings**

  `د† : { k // âˆƒ q, â€–Q.weight k qâ€– = 1 } â†ھ Fin P.basisCount`,
  `دˆ : { j // âˆƒ q, â€–P.weight j qâ€– = 1 } â†ھ Fin Q.basisCount`.

Injectivity is the CPSV16 آ§II.C lines 1184â€“1186 conclusion: two
unit-modulus sectors of `Q` that match the SAME sector `j` of `P`
would force two sectors of `Q` to be gauge-phase equivalent through
the common centre `P.basis j`, contradicting `basis_distinct` of `Q`.

## Scoping note (honest scoping per the task brief)

The user-requested literal form `خ² : UnitQ â‰ƒ UnitP` (a bijection
between the unit-modulus Finsets) requires an additional argument that
the matched `j` lies in `UnitP`, i.e. that the matched sector of `P`
also carries a unit-modulus weight.  That step is **not** discharged by
the Phase B-خ± non-decay output alone (`mpvOverlap` is on the *basis*
tensors, not on the weighted sectors); it requires the per-sector
weight-equivariance argument of CPSV16 Lemma `equalMPS` (lines 1148â€“1167)
combined with the gauge-phase identity on weighted sectors.  Phase B-خ²
delivers the *symmetric injective matching*, which is the direct
formalisation of the paper's `g_a â‰¥ g_b âˆ§ g_b â‰¥ g_a` step on the
unit-modulus subsets; the upgrade to `UnitQ â‰ƒ UnitP` is deferred to a
later phase that lifts the matching from basis-MPV non-decay to weight
